## By Design Speciality

### Product Designer

What companies look for:
- End-to-end ownership (research → shipped feature)
- Collaboration with PM and eng
- Impact on product metrics
- Systems thinking

Key CV language to include:
```
"Owned the end-to-end design of..."
"Collaborated with PM and engineering to define requirements..."
"Shipped [feature] to [X] users, resulting in..."
"Led discovery through usability testing, uncovering..."
"Contributed to / maintained the design system..."
```

### UX Designer

What companies look for:
- Research fluency (generative + evaluative)
- Synthesis and insight generation
- Information architecture
- Cross-functional influence through user data

Key CV language to include:
```
"Conducted 12 in-depth interviews with [user type], synthesised into..."
"Ran moderated usability tests on [product], identifying [N] critical issues"
"Created journey maps and service blueprints for..."
"Facilitated design sprints and workshops with [X] stakeholders"
"Defined IA and navigation for [product area]..."
```

### UI / Visual Designer

What companies look for:
- Visual craft and taste
- Figma/design tool mastery
- Design system component ownership
- Consistency at scale

Key CV language to include:
```
"Designed and shipped [N] components to the design system"
"Established visual language / design guidelines for..."
"Created responsive UI across mobile, tablet, desktop using Figma"
"Collaborated with brand team to align product UI with brand identity"
"Conducted visual QA with engineering to ensure pixel-perfect output"
```

